<TITLE> 13 bridges around Dhaka to be pulled down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 31 (bdnews24.com)  A government taskforce has identified 13 bridgesin and around Dhaka to be pulled down and rebuilt to make waterways underneath them more pliable for large water vessels. The high level taskforce headed by shipping minister Shahjahan Khan asked relevant government authorities on Wednesday to pull down the bridges. Shahjahan told reporters after the task force had identified 15 low-level bridges around Dhaka, of which only two lie 25 feet above than flood level. The other 13Gabtali Bailey Bridge on the Turag river, Ashulia Bridge, the still under construction Dhaur-2 on Tongi canal, Prottasa/Noinichala Bailey Bridge, Kamarpara Bridge, Tongi Road Bridge (east and west section), Tongi Rail Bridge 1 and 2, the still under construction Rupgonj Bridge on the Balu river, Ishapur Bailey Bridge, Kayetpara Bridge and Demra Bridgewill be demolished under this order. These bridges create obstruction for water transport during the flood season, Khan said. The will rebuilt following the standard height of 25 ft above the flood level, he said. The order has been sent for permission of the other ministries of the government, the minister added. bd
